Package com.example.appointment

Class Customer

java.lang.Object
com.example.appointment.Customer
public class Customer extends Object
A class to create a customer object. Specific data is associated with each customer, and one customer is associated with each appointment.

  • Constructor Details

    • Customer

      public Customer(int customerID, String customerName, String address, String postalCode, String phone, ZonedDateTime createDate, String createdBy, ZonedDateTime lastUpdate, String lastUpdatedBy, int divisionID)
      A constructor for creating a unique customer object. The customer has specific data for its name and location, and can be tied to a specific appointment.
      Parameters:
      customerID - The ID value for this customer.
      customerName - The name for the customer.
      address - The address for the customer. Restricted depending on its country.
      postalCode - The postal code for the customer. Restricted depending on its country.
      phone - The phone number for the customer. Restricted depending on its country.
      createDate - Data for the customer includes the creation date, creation time and time zone.
      createdBy - The username that created the customer.
      lastUpdate - Data for the customer includes the last updated date, last updated time and time zone.
      lastUpdatedBy - The username that last updated the customer.
      divisionID - An ID representing the state/province/territory of the customer.
